# Rule 05 ‚Äî PrimeVue Ecosystem Guardrails

AI agents frequently (a) reach for native HTML elements instead of PrimeVue components, (b) hallucinate prop/event/slot names from outdated training data, and (c) use `:deep()` CSS overrides instead of the PT system. This rule enforces three pillars of defense.

> **Stack**: PrimeVue v4.5+ Styled Mode. All components are auto-imported (Rule 08).
> **Companion rule**: For PT styling methodology ‚Üí `07-primevue-styled-pt.mdc`.

---

## PILLAR 1 ‚Äî Strict Component Substitution

### 1.1 ABSOLUTE RULE

In `src/views/`, `src/components/`, and `src/layouts/`, native HTML interactive/data/feedback elements are **FORBIDDEN** when a PrimeVue equivalent exists.

**Permitted native elements** (structural/semantic only): `<div>`, `<span>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<footer>`, `<main>`, `<nav>`, `<aside>`, `<article>`, `<ul>`, `<ol>`, `<li>`, `<label>`, `<form>`, `<h1>`‚Äì`<h6>`, `<p>`, `<a>` (external links only ‚Äî internal navigation MUST use `<RouterLink>`).

**[LAW] Form Sovereignty:**
Inside `src/views/**` (Business Pages), native `<form>` is FORBIDDEN. MUST use `<ProForm>` for forms with 2+ fields. Single-field trivial cases may use standalone PrimeVue controls.

