## AI Standard Operating Procedure ‚Äî PrimeVue UI Tasks

<ai_sop>

### Step 1 ‚Äî ELEMENT AUDIT

For every element in `<template>`:
1. Check the Substitution Table (Section 1.2). PrimeVue equivalent exists? ‚Üí Use it.
2. No equivalent? ‚Üí Native element is permitted.
3. Unsure about v4 name? ‚Üí Check `src/types/components.d.ts`.

### Step 2 ‚Äî API VERIFICATION

1. Classify the component by Tier (Section 2.3).
2. **Tier 1** ‚Üí Proceed from memory. Basic props (`label`, `icon`, `severity`, `disabled`, `v-model`) are stable.
3. **Tier 2** ‚Üí If using more than 3 props or any slot, fetch the docs page.
4. **Tier 3** ‚Üí ALWAYS fetch `https://primevue.org/[component]` before writing the first line.

### Step 3 ‚Äî PT PRESET CHECK

1. Check `src/utils/theme/ptPresets/formControlsPt.ts` and `menuPt.ts`.
2. Check `src/utils/theme/presetComponents/`.
3. Global PT exists? ‚Üí Local `:pt` should ADD, not DUPLICATE.
4. Need visual customization? ‚Üí Use `:pt` with UnoCSS semantic tokens (Rule 07).
5. **NEVER** write `<style scoped>` with `:deep(.p-*)` selectors.

### Step 4 ‚Äî COMPOUND COMPONENT CHECK

PrimeVue v4 restructured several components from monolithic to compound:
- `Tabs` ‚Üí `<Tabs>` + `<TabList>` + `<Tab>` + `<TabPanels>` + `<TabPanel>`
- `Stepper` ‚Üí `<Stepper>` + `<StepList>` + `<Step>` + `<StepPanels>` + `<StepPanel>`
- `Accordion` ‚Üí `<Accordion>` + `<AccordionPanel>` + `<AccordionHeader>` + `<AccordionContent>`

Verify you are using the COMPOUND structure, not the legacy monolithic API.

### Step 5 ‚Äî PRE-OUTPUT CHECKLIST

Before finalizing any PrimeVue template output:

- [ ] No native `<button>`, `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>`, `<table>`, `<dialog>`, `<progress>` in business code
- [ ] No v3 component names (`Dropdown`, `Calendar`, `InputSwitch`, `Sidebar`, `TabView`, `Steps`)
- [ ] All Tier 3 component APIs verified against PrimeVue v4 docs
- [ ] No `:deep(.p-*)` in `<style scoped>` outside documented exceptions
- [ ] Global PT presets checked ‚Äî no conflict with local `:pt`
- [ ] Compound component structure used for Tabs / Stepper / Accordion
- [ ] `v-model` used for two-way binding (not `:value` + `@change` separately)
- [ ] Complex forms use `<ProForm>` schema engine when appropriate (Rule 02)
- [ ] Complex tables use `<ProTable>` when appropriate (Rule 02)

</ai_sop>
